FBIS4-21226 "jptdd017__l94069" JPRS-TDD-94-017-L JPRS Narcotics 15 April 1994 AFRICA SOUTH AFRICA South Africans Returning From Bangkok, U.S. Arrested for South Africans Returning From Bangkok, U.S. Arrested for Possessing Cocaine MB1504113294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1042 GMT 15 Apr 94 MB1504113294 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Johannesburg April 15 SAPA -- Police arrested a 35-year-old man at Johannesburg's Jan Smuts Airport on Friday after 6 kg of cocaine with street value of R[Rand]2.1 million was discovered in a false compartment of his briefcase. The man, a South African, was returning from Bangkok. A 23-year-old South African on his way back from the United State was arrested as he re-entered the country on Thursday with 1 kg of cocaine hidden in his briefcase. Both men are due to appear in the Kempton Park magistrate's court on Monday.
